        "created_at": "2025-09-10T02:50:24.815Z",
        "cooked": "<p>currently the windows installer silently installs to:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">C:\\Users\\myUser\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\signal-desktop\n</code></pre>\n<p>even when passing the /ALLUSERS option to the installer.</p>\n<p>So on multiuser machines each user has to install its own app even though windows fully supports central apps with user space user data.</p>\n<p>this makes it impossible to have a secure installation where an admin-role does the central app installation and the user has a user-rights only account which only handles user data (as Unix-style systems usually are setup).</p>\n<p>There is a winget issue that is blocked due to this feature.</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox githubissue\" data-onebox-src=\"https://github.com/microsoft/winget-pkgs/issues/95387\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/microsoft/winget-pkgs/issues/95387\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">github.com/microsoft/winget-pkgs</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"github-row\">\n  <div class=\"github-icon-container\" title=\"Issue\" data-github-private-repo=\"false\">\n\t  <svg width=\"60\" height=\"60\" class=\"github-icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 14 16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M7 2.3c3.14 0 5.7 2.56 5.7 5.7s-2.56 5.7-5.7 5.7A5.71 5.71 0 0 1 1.3 8c0-3.14 2.56-5.7 5.7-5.7zM7 1C3.14 1 0 4.14 0 8s3.14 7 7 7 7-3.14 7-7-3.14-7-7-7zm1 3H6v5h2V4zm0 6H6v2h2v-2z\"></path></svg>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-info-container\">\n    <h4>\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/microsoft/winget-pkgs/issues/95387\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">[Package Issue]: OpenWhisperSystems.Signal manifest claims to support scope=machine, but the installer does not actually support that</a>\n    </h4>\n\n    <div class=\"github-info\">\n      <div class=\"date\">\n        opened <span class=\"discourse-local-date\" data-format=\"ll\" data-date=\"2023-02-02\" data-time=\"05:39:44\" data-timezone=\"UTC\">05:39AM - 02 Feb 23 UTC</span>\n      </div>\n\n\n      <div class=\"user\">\n        <a href=\"https://github.com/MarcoPeraza\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">\n          <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/5/7/57d4a5794dc7ad332b0b0b3985b650e72612782f.png\" class=\"onebox-avatar-inline\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" data-dominant-color=\"DBDBDB\">\n          MarcoPeraza\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"labels\">\n        <span style=\"display:inline-block;margin-top:2px;background-color: #B8B8B8;padding: 2px;border-radius: 4px;color: #fff;margin-left: 3px;\">\n          Issue-Bug\n        </span>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-row\">\n    <p class=\"github-body-container\">### Please confirm these before moving forward\n\n- [X] I have searched for my i<span class=\"show-more-container\"><a href=\"\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"show-more\">…</a></span><span class=\"excerpt hidden\">ssue and not found a work-in-progress/duplicate/resolved issue.\n- [X] I have not been informed if the issue is resolved in a preview version of the winget client.\n\n### Category of the issue\n\nInstallation issue.\n\n### Brief description of your issue\n\nThe manifest for OpenWhisperSystems.Signal supports machine-wide installs, passing /ALLUSERS to the signal installer exe. But the Signal installer exe itself does not support such an option. No matter what you do, it still installs only for the current user, to %localappdata%\\Programs\\signal-desktop. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`winget install -e OpenWhisperSystems.Signal --scope machine`\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nSignal is installed inside the current user's profile: %localappdata%\\Programs\\signal-desktop\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSignal is installed systemwide, but Signal itself does not support that.\n\n### Environment\n\n```shell\nWindows Package Manager (Preview) v1.5.0-preview\nCopyright (c) Microsoft Corporation. All rights reserved.\n\nWindows: Windows.Desktop v10.0.22621.1105\nSystem Architecture: X64\n\nLogs: %TEMP%\\WinGet\\defaultState\n\nUser Settings: %LOCALAPPDATA%\\Microsoft\\WinGet\\Settings\\defaultState\\settings.json\n```\n\n\n### Screenshots and Logs\n\n_No response_</span></p>\n  </div>\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n",
